text.section:
The department shall administer and enforce the provisions of this chapter and promulgate administrative regulations to carry out the provisions of this chapter and in the administrative regulations may prescribe methods to be used in the storage of fertilizers, and the storage and application of pesticides. Where the department finds that the administrative regulations are necessary to carry out the purpose and intent of this chapter, the administrative regulations may relate to the time, place, manner, and method of storage and application of the pesticides and storage of fertilizers, may restrict or prohibit use of pesticides in designated areas during specified periods of time, and shall encompass all reasonable factors which the department deems necessary to prevent damage or injury by drift or misapplication to:
Plants, including forage plants, on adjacent or nearby lands;
Wildlife in the adjoining or nearby areas;
Fish and other aquatic life in waters in reasonable proximity to the area to be treated; and
Pollinating insects, animals, or persons.
